# GHL Iframe Embed — Test Instructions

Skill 62 (Cinematic and Web Funnel Engine), build unit U18, spec Section 14.2.

- Project: `__CWFE_PROJECT_SLUG__`
- Hosted (child) origin: `__CWFE_CHILD_ORIGIN__`
- Allowed parent (ancestor) origins: `__CWFE_ALLOWED_ORIGINS_JSON__`
- Fallback URL: `__CWFE_FALLBACK_URL__`
- Package generated: `__CWFE_GENERATED_AT__`

## Before you start

1. Paste `host-snippet.html` into a GHL page's Custom HTML/Code element.
2. Confirm the Vercel-hosted (child) deployment's own response headers
   include `Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors ...` for exactly the
   allowed origins above — see `csp-headers.json` in this package for the
   exact header value and a ready-to-merge `vercel.json` fragment. GHL
   cannot set this header for you; it must be configured on the hosted app.

## Desktop

- [ ] Page loads with no nested/inner scrollbar on the iframe.
- [ ] Scrolling the GHL page scrolls the embedded experience — no scroll
      trap, no place where the page appears "stuck".
- [ ] The iframe's height grows/shrinks to track content as you scroll
      (watch for clipped content at the bottom of any section — that would
      mean a resize message was missed).
- [ ] Every CTA inside the iframe is fully visible and clickable.
- [ ] Browser devtools console shows no cross-origin postMessage errors and
      no CSP `frame-ancestors` violation.

## Mobile (representative viewport, e.g. 390x844)

- [ ] No horizontal scrollbar appears on the GHL page.
- [ ] No independent vertical scrollbar appears inside the iframe itself.
- [ ] The always-visible fallback link below the iframe opens the direct
      hosted URL (`__CWFE_FALLBACK_URL__`).

## Fallback path

- [ ] With JavaScript disabled, the `<noscript>` fallback link is visible
      and points to `__CWFE_FALLBACK_URL__`.
- [ ] Blocking/erroring the iframe request (devtools network throttling)
      still leaves the always-visible fallback link functional.

## Automated (Playwright GHL-iframe harness, spec 19.3)

Run the skill's Playwright suite against a host page that embeds
`host-snippet.html` and assert:

- no element on the host page produces its own scrollbar for the iframe
  content (`overflow-y` computed style on `.cwfe-embed-iframe` is never
  `scroll`/`auto` while its `scrollHeight` exceeds `clientHeight`);
- `window.__cwfeScrollDebug` (exposed by the embedded child page per spec
  13.2) advances as the harness scrolls the host page;
- a simulated `postMessage` from an origin NOT in the allowed list above is
  ignored (no height change, no `cwfe:conversion` event fires).
